15\u20132016)\n* {{flagicon|USA}} [[Jack Stefanowski]] (2016, interim)\n* {{flagicon|Spain}} [[Carlos Garc\u00eda Cantarero]] (2016\u20132018)\n* {{flagicon|Honduras}} [[Amado Guevara]] (2018\u20132019)\n* {{flagicon|Puerto Rico}} [[Elgy Morales]] (2019\u2013present)<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://us.soccerway.com/coaches/elgy-morales/294747/|title=Puerto Rico - E. Morales - Profile with news, career statistics and history - Soccerway|website=us.soccerway.com|access-date=2020-02-22}}</ref>\n{{col-end}}\n\n== See also ==\n{{portal|Association football|Puerto Rico}}\n* [[Puerto Rico national under-20 football team]]\n* [[Puerto Rico women's national football team]]\n* [[Football in Puerto Rico]]\n\n== References ==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n== External links ==\n* [https://www.fifa.com/associations/association=pur/index.html Puerto Rico web page] at FIFA.com\n* [http://www.rsssf.com/tablesp/prico-intres.html Puerto Rico List of International Matches] at RSSSF.com\n* [http://www.fedefutbolpr.com/ Official site: Federaci\u00f3n Puertorrique\u00f1a de F\u00fatbol]\n\n{{Football in Puerto Rico}}\n{{CONCACAF teams}}\n{{National sports teams of Puerto Rico}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Puerto Rico National Football Team}}\n[[Category:Puerto Rico national football team| ]]\n[[Category:Caribbean national association football teams]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|National association football team}}\n{{About|the men's team|the women's team|Puerto Rico women's national football team}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=November 2019}}\n{{Infobox national football team\n| Name               = Puerto Rico\n| Nickname           = {{nowrap|{{lang|es|El Hurac\u00e1n Azul}}<br />''(The Blue Hurricane)''}}\n| Badge              = \n| Badge_size         = 190px\n| Association        = [[Puerto Rican Football Federation|''Federaci\u00f3n Puertorrique\u00f1a de F\u00fatbol'']] (FPF)\n| Confederation      = [[CONCACAF]] (North America)\n| Sub-confederation  = [[Caribbean Football Union|CFU]] (Caribbean)\n| Coach       